<paragraph id="8BEA36C46A6FFFB1288AFB5EFD72FB77" blockId="1.[151,1436,902,1231]" box="[151,763,1209,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB1288AFB5EFE91FB77" box="[151,280,1209,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB1288AFB5EFE91FB77" box="[151,280,1209,1231]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Tachydromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, authors, not Meigen, 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB129E2FB5DFDBDFB77" box="[511,564,1210,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="1803.0">1803</number>
, misidentifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36C46A6FFFB1288AFB1BFEBDFA54" blockId="1.[151,1437,1276,1948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB1288AFB1BFE08FAAC" bold="true" box="[151,385,1276,1300]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Notes on synonymy</emphasis>
. When examining 
<typeStatus id="54EE88666A6FFFB12A40FB1AFD04FAAD" box="[605,653,1277,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
materials of the species assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12C2BFB1BFB7AFAAC" box="[1078,1267,1276,1300]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Charadrodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12C2BFB1BFB7AFAAC" box="[1078,1267,1276,1300]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Charadrodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we found that actually they belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12A16FAC7FC45FA8F" authority="Macquart. Melander (1928)" authorityName="Macquart. Melander" authorityYear="1928" box="[523,972,1311,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12A16FAC7FD18FA80" box="[523,657,1312,1336]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Platypalpus</emphasis>
Macquart. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B356A6FFFB12B0DFAF8FC45FA8F" author="Melander" box="[784,972,1311,1335]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" refString="Melander, A. L. (1928) Diptera, Fam. Empididae. In: Wytsman, P. (Ed.), Genera Insectorum Fasc. 185. Louis Desmet- Verteneuil, Bruxelles, 434 pp." type="book" year="1928">
Melander (
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB12B94FAF8FC4AFA8F" box="[905,963,1311,1335]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="1928.0">1928</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
did not provide any comparative analysis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB128ABFAA3FEFDFAE4" box="[182,372,1348,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Charadrodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB128ABFAA3FEFDFAE4" box="[182,372,1348,1372]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Charadrodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but his key to the genera and subgenera of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12B97FAA3FBC9FAE4" box="[906,1088,1348,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tachydromiinae">Tachydromiinae</taxonomicName>
(l.c.: 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB12C9EFAA3FB27FAE4" box="[1155,1198,1348,1372]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="270.0">270</number>
) indicates diagnostic features that Melander thought to be crucial to erect a separate genus: first basal cell equal to or longer than the second, anal cell not formed; face narrower than frons; two pairs each of ocellar and vertical bristles; arista apical; humeri constricted; legs not evidently bristly; cheeks linear; notum with coarse hairs but no strong anterior dorsocentrals.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36C46A6FFFB128DAFA1FFC11F8B4" blockId="1.[151,1437,1276,1948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
It is evident that none of the characters applied by Melander could be used to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12CC2FA1FFA15F9A8" box="[1247,1436,1528,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Charadrodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12CC2FA1FFA15F9A8" box="[1247,1436,1528,1552]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Charadrodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB128C9F9FBFED3F98C" box="[212,346,1564,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB128C9F9FBFED3F98C" box="[212,346,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Platypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Relative lengths of cells br and bm of the wing (= first and second basal cells) are quite variable in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB128A6F9A7FEC8F9E0" box="[187,321,1600,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB128A6F9A7FEC8F9E0" box="[187,321,1600,1624]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Platypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including North American species (e.g., Chillcott 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB12BB6F9D8FC6EF9EF" box="[939,999,1599,1623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="1962.0">1962</number>
: 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB12BE7F9D8FBAFF9EF" box="[1018,1062,1599,1623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="117.0">117</number>
, figs. 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB12C65F9D8FB3AF9EF" box="[1144,1203,1599,1623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B356A6FFFB12CDBF9D8FAE9F9EF" author="Chvala" box="[1222,1376,1599,1623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" refString="Chvala, M. (1975) The Tachydromiinae (Dipt. Empididae) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 3, 1 - 336." type="journal article" year="1975">
Chvála 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB12D39F9D8FAE9F9EF" box="[1316,1376,1599,1623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB1288AF983FF77F9C4" box="[151,254,1636,1660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="710.5" valueMax="747.0" valueMin="674.0">674–747</number>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB1292EF983FE30F9C4" box="[307,441,1636,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB1292EF983FE30F9C4" box="[307,441,1636,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Platypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the anal cell (or cell cu 
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12AD1F982FD53F9C4" box="[716,730,1637,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">p</emphasis>
) is usually closed (anal vein distinct basally) but rarely (e.g., some species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12988F96EFDACF918" box="[405,549,1672,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hackmani">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12988F96EFDACF918" box="[405,549,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. hackmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) it is not quite formed (anal vein wanting or evanescent basally). Furthermore, the anal vein is distinct in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12A45F94AFD5BF97C" box="[600,722,1708,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arnaudi">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12A45F94AFD5BF97C" box="[600,722,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">C. arnaudi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation id="136E2A416A6FFFB12B1BF94BFCC0F97C" box="[774,841,1708,1732]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1818,1841]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,687,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1361,682,1797]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Platypalpus arnaudi (Melander), male. 1. habitus, lateral view. 2. wing, dorsal view. 3. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 4. epandrium with cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 5. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282719/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9D24E36A6FFFB12B27F94BFCC0F97C" box="[826,841,1708,1732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) and evanescent in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12CC2F94BFA15F97C" box="[1247,1436,1708,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Charadrodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12CC2F94BFA15F97C" box="[1247,1436,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Charadrodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="136E2A416A6FFFB12882F928FF67F95F" box="[159,238,1743,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1249,1272]" captionTargetBox="[272,1314,465,1228]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1332,445,1228]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 6. Platypalpus microphona (Melander), habitus, female (paralectotype), lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282720/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136E2A416A6FFFB128E7F928FE83F95F" box="[250,266,1743,1767]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[155,1427,477,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[265,1321,1092,1829]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Platypalpus syletor (Melander). 7. apical part of right epandrial lamella, ventral view. 8. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 9. cerci and epandrium, dorsal view. 10. left epandrial lamella, lateral view. 11. habitus, female (holotype), lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282721/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">7</figureCitation>
). Finally, the length of ocellar bristles varies in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12B03F937FC2DF950" box="[798,932,1744,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12B03F937FC2DF950" box="[798,932,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Platypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and even in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12C2FF937FB66F950" box="[1074,1263,1744,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Charadrodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12C2FF937FB66F950" box="[1074,1263,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Charadrodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB1288AF913FEDDF8B4" box="[151,340,1780,1804]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Charadrodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB1288AF913FEDDF8B4" box="[151,340,1780,1804]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Charadrodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is viewed here as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12B16F913FC18F8B4" box="[779,913,1780,1804]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12B16F913FC18F8B4" box="[779,913,1780,1804]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Platypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36C46A6FFFB128DAF8F0FC57F824" blockId="1.[151,1437,1276,1948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12955F8FFFE60F888" box="[328,489,1816,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12955F8FFFE60F888" box="[328,489,1816,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Chersodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB12A9CF8FFFCB6F888" box="[641,831,1816,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Charadrodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAD66A6FFFB12A9CF8FFFCB6F888" box="[641,831,1816,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Charadrodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was distinguished in Melander’s key belongs to the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D476A6FFFB128CCF8DBFEB2F8EC" box="[209,315,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Drapetini">Drapetini</taxonomicName>
